<h1>Noun Sentences</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N{{}}@HI{{desu}}.
<li> @N{{}}@HI{{da}}.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
A noun sentence is one which ends in a noun followed by a form of the <a href="grammar-copula.html">copula</a>.
The copula inflects to express the politeness level and whether the sentence is in the past or in the negative.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinouha@KJ{{rain}}deshita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yesterday it rained.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/><br/>

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinouno@KJ{{test^verification}}ha @KJ{{simplicity^simple}}jaarimasendeshita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Yesterday's exam was not easy.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

